          "date": "2016-07-12 01:40:44.000000000",
          "tz": -420
        },
        "subject": "LU-7734 lnet: fix routing selection",
        "message": "LU-7734 lnet: fix routing selection\n\nWhen running through the best_ni selection, the algorithm walks\nthrough each net in the peer net list. If a peer net is local\nfollowed by a peer net which is remote, the current algorithm would\nselect the best_ni for the local network, but still set routing to\ntrue which sends the message out of the wrong local ni, and it\nnever reaches the destination.\n\nThe fix is to keep track when a best_ni on a local network is\npreferred over a best_ni for a gateway and set routing off.\n\nSigned-off-by: Amir Shehata <amir.shehata@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I3bec4809cc7478cce533591f4519f0c262be40f0\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/multi-rail"
    }
